reviews.review_text: Buck Dancers Choice Sound quality is pretty good..Always love a China>Rider to end 1st set. A well played 2nd set..though I like to hear more than 2 songs before Drums>Space..Give it a whirl

OMG! Brent on Gimmie Some Lovin" !!! Now I was at this show. It was my first effort at taping. It went mostly horrible! Highlites of that show was Drums/Space and...Gimmie Some Lovin"! Wow! Brent was all over on the organ on that one. Man! Was he diggin' in there! And them growls near the end! With Phil and Jerry. Yikes! Brent was never used enough. He could've done a great Hard To Handle! What might have been. Oh well! At least he did the BEST EVER Gimmie! Yowza! so, 5 stars just for that!

These Scotton Walker things These folks, whoever they may, have given us a lot of stuff that wouldn't be here, a lot of which I attended so I am always looking for SBDs. Such as 4 21 84 which has no SBD. But, was the band into Dolby then or something, to me some of them from these two are fuzzed or dolby'd out. maybe its me, maybe I want what doesn't exist, maybe someone screwed up that's likely, or is that noise in my head bothering you also? This one doesn't have it as much as some of the 84 shows.

Box o Rain vocal echo There is an echo in the vocal track of Box of Rain I did not hear anywhere else on this one. It is as if Healy REALLY cranked up the reverb/delay, or, more probably, print through on the masters or a tape copy

If they're only playing 2 songs before drums ... It's nice if one of them is a hot 15+ minute Playin'.  Other highlights include Half-Step, China>Rider (although Weir's completely fudging his part in China Cat), Gimme Some, and Uncle John's.  A pretty strong Drums>Space also.  The rest is pretty average.  The sound is excellent -- listen through WinAmp and turn up the upper mid-range, especially in Drums.  

Does anyone remember what Bob was rambling about during Good Lovin'?  Something about a radioactive cloud hanging over the place and making everyone glow in the dark.  It was still in Cold War times, Reagan, "We begin bombing in five minutes," Grenada, Panama, etc.

these cal expo shows are primo all sorts of gems in '86 many pass over. really like these 5/3 and 5/4 shows -- both different, both excellent. this 5/4 show rocks right out of the gate w a 'ron' mention on saturday nite... best part of show imo is post drums UJB thru Good Lovin', which I give 5 stars... and nice Box 'o Rain encore.
